data.content:
`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a built-in .NET MAUI property. You need two things:

### 1. Set `IgnoreSafeArea` on the view (iOS)
Apply it to the `Image` or its parent layout, not the page:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui" ...>
    <Grid IgnoreSafeArea="True">
        <Image Source="photo.jpg"
               Aspect="AspectFill" />
    </Grid>
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. Go edge-to-edge on Android
In your `MainActivity.cs`, make the status/nav bars transparent:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    if (Window is not null)
    {
        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);
        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);

        // Draw behind system bars
        AndroidX.Core.View.WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);
    }
}
```

> **Note (.NET 10 / Android 15+):** Edge-to-edge is enforced by default on apps targeting API 35+, so `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(false)` may already be the default. You still need transparent bar colors and `IgnoreSafeArea="True"` on the MAUI side.

**TL;DR:** `IgnoreSafeArea="True"` on the layout handles iOS; transparent system bars + `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(false)` handles Android.
